attr.attrdef: Feature geometry.
Address Prefix Direction - used by ESRI geocoder
Address Prefix Type - normally for STH and CTH - used by ESRI geocoder
Address Street Name - street names - used by ESRI geocoder
Address Suffix Type - normally Ave, Dr, etc. - used by ESRI geocoder
Address Suffix Direction - Value of 'W' indicates private road, no other values used in Adams County - Used to ID pvt roads in Spillman
Concatenation of the preceding columns to form a readable street name - used by ESRI geocoder, Spillman and for labeling
Side of the segment where addresses are found - B = both, NULL/Empty string = both, O = odd, E = even
Left Prefix - Prefix given to addresses found on the left side of the road - in Adams County this is only used for north/south roads in the "short section" along the north edge of T16N
Right Prefix - Prefix given to addresses found on the right side of the road - in Adams County this is only used for north/south roads in the "short section" along the north edge of T16N
Flag that identifies segments to be excluded in Spillman _______ validation - it identifies valid deviations from the standard format.
Flag used to exclude the row from having its features automatically populated by the Spillman Auto-Populate Left/Right Fields from Polygon Layers tool
Unknown - no rows have a value in this column
Minor Civil Division Code - number identifying the MCD
City Code - ONLY for rows with an alias
Prefix given to addresses - in Adams County this is only used for north/south roads in the "short section" along the north edge of T16N
Beginning Number of the segment, ONLY for rows with an alias
End Number of the segment, ONLY for rows with an alias
Hyperlink - unknown, no rows have a value in this column
Left City Code - city code found on the left side of the segment - Spillman
Right City Code - city code found on the right side of the segment - Spillman
Left ZIP Code - ZIP code found on the left side of the segment - Spillman
Right ZIP Code - ZIP code found on the right side of the segment - Spillman
Beginning of address range on the left side of the segment - Spillman
End of address range on the left side of the segment - Spillman
Beginning of address range on the right side of the segment - Spillman
End of address range on the right side of the segment - Spillman
Law Dispatch Zone found on the left side of the segment - Spillman
Law Dispatch Zone found on the right side of the segment - Spillman
Law Reporting Area found on the left side of the segment - Spillman
Law Reporting Area found on the right side of the segment - Spillman
Fire Dispatch Zone found on the left side of the segment - Spillman
Fire Dispatch Zone found on the right side of the segment - Spillman
EMS Dispatch Zone found on the left side of the segment - Spillman
EMS Dispatch Zone found on the right side of the segment - Spillman
Beginning of address range on the left side of the segment - Alphanumeric format with leading address prefix - ESRI geocoder
Ene of address range on the left side of the segment - Alphanumeric format with leading address prefix - ESRI geocoder
Beginning of address range on the right side of the segment - Alphanumeric format with leading address prefix - ESRI geocoder
End of address range on the right side of the segment - Alphanumeric format with leading address prefix - ESRI geocoder
Global ID automatically assigned by ArcGIS to allow for replication
Unknown - values IN 1, 2, 3
Internal feature number.

attrdomv.udom: Sequential unique whole numbers that are automatically generated.

attr.attrdef: Key value used to join the SDE Streets feature class to the streets shapefile. Calculated thus: [street]& [GC_From_L]& [GC_To_L]& [GC_From_R]& [GC_To_R]
Length of feature in internal units.

attrdomv.udom: Positive real numbers that are automatically generated.

overview.eaover: Attribute information remains the same as given by the author of the data.
